SUMMARY:Book Discussion
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School class. Click here to register on 
 the Adult School website\n\nJoin avid readers to discuss themes\, plots and 
 characters of selected books. Participate in the stimulating exchange of 
 ideas\, observations and reactions to the current selections. The books 
 we'll be reading are:\n\nMarch 4:  "The Antidote" by Karen Russell\nMarch 
 18:  "The House of Mirth" by Edith Wharton\nApril 8 : "The Emperor of 
 Gladness by Ocean Vuong\nApril 22: "Sense & Sensibility" by Jane 
 Austen\nMay 6: "Orbital" by Samantha Harvey\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Tower Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Book Discussion
