DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T113000
SUMMARY:Verona Park
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nJOIN US FOR A WALK\n\nWe will meet at the benche
 s in front of the boathouse.\n\nWe will walk the loop around the park. The
  goal will be at least three miles\, but there is plenty of opportunity to
  stop or continue to fit your personal goals.\n\nWe will be walking on a p
 aved surface.\n\nWe walk at a medium speed.\n\nPlease plan to arrive 5 min
 utes **early** so that we can **start on time.**\n\nVerona Park is 54.32 a
 cres with a lake running through it. It is bordered by Lakeside and Bloomf
 ield Avenues in the southern part of Verona. It is the fifth largest park 
 in the Essex County system\, making it a great place to walk.\n\nDisclaime
 r: If you join us for a hike\, please understand that you are responsible 
 for your own preparedness and well-being and will hold no one else liable 
 in case of injury or mishap. Event will be canceled in the event of extrem
 e weather.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313605205/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260302T180319Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T180319Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: South Mountain Conservancy": "https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313605598/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_somocon
X-SOURCE:Meetup: South Mountain Conservancy
UID:event_313605598@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260305T024114Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T130000
SUMMARY:👠From Heels to Boots - IWD Hike w/Ivette ~ 5-6 miles🥾\nfor 5
 0+ Community 
DESCRIPTION:South Mountain Conservancy Activities Meetup Group\n**50+ hike
  celebrating International Women's Day - open to both\, women and men.**\n
 \n**We aren't just hitting the trails for the views\; we are walking with 
 the intention of celebrating the incredible milestones women have achieved
  across every field.**\n_This hike is to remind us of women’s resilience
  and the struggle for women’s rights to the uphill trail\, sometimes roc
 ky\, requiring endurance\, but offering a better perspective of the **“t
 he higher you go”.**_\n\nAll participants will receive a ribbon to honor
  a special lady in their life. We will flag the trail with Purple Ribbons 
 in recognition of the Women’s History Month in USA.\nThe flags will stay
  on for the duration of the month for visitors to follow them from Tulip S
 prings to Hemlock Falls Over the Girl Scout bridge and back to Tulip Sprin
 gs via Turtleback trail.\n\nThis is a social event so a steady\, but moder
 ate pace will be maintained to enjoy nature and carry a conversation.• M
 ust be able to walk 6 miles.• No dogs please.• Times are our best esti
 mates\, but can vary depending on conditions\, and the size or pace of the
  group.\n\n**What to bring for a Hike:** Ice Spikes\, Water\, Gatorade\, H
 iking Shoes or Boots (no sneakers)\, Snacks\, Trekking Poles (optional)\, 
 Bug Spray\, Sunscreen\, and a Talking Point! Dress for the weather and in 
 Light Layers. Steady rain or snow cancels the hike.\n\n**NOTE:** You are r
 esponsible for bringing appropriate gear\, supplies\, clothing\, necessary
  medication\, EpiPen and first aid kit.\n\n**\\*****\\*****\\* In register
 ing for this or any other South Mountain Conservancy (SMC) programs in 202
 6 online\, I hereby release and agree to hold the SMC\, its volunteers\, s
 taff and Board of Trustees\, harmless from and waive on behalf of myself\,
  my heirs\, and any personal representatives any and all causes of action\
 , claims\, demands\, damages\, costs\, expenses and compensation for damag
 e or loss to myself and/or property that may be caused by any act\, or fai
 lure to act\, in this SMC activity\, or that may otherwise arise in any wa
 y in connection with any other SMC activity. I understand that this releas
 e discharges the SMC from any liability or claim that I\, my heirs\, or an
 y personal representatives\, may have against the SMC with respect to any 
 bodily injury\, illness\, death\, medical treatment\, or property damage t
 hat may arise from\, or in connection to\, any SMC program. This liability
  waiver and release extends to the SMC along with Essex County and its sta
 ff and any other affiliated organization or SMC partner. I also understand
  that by signing below I approve the possible use of photos of me at this 
 SMC event on social media or in promotional materials.\n**BY REGISTERING F
 OR THIS HIKE I attest I am in good health and attest that I: Am not experi
 encing any symptoms of illness such as cough\, shortness of breath or diff
 iculty breathing\, fever\, chills\, repeated shaking with chills\, muscle 
 pain\, headache\, sore throat\, or new loss of taste or smell.**\nAm follo
 wing all CDC recommended guidelines\, above\, and limiting my exposure to 
 the novel coronavirus/COVID-19.\n\\# Arrival\\\, Weather\\\, & Cancellatio
 ns\nPlease come to the starting point 10 minutes ahead of time so the hike
  can start promptly. Times are our best estimates\; they can vary dependin
 g on conditions\, and the size and pace of a group. If you have any questi
 ons\, call the leader.\n- Temperatures above 90 degrees and steady rain/sn
 ow cancels\, but intermittent drizzle does not. **You will not be notified
 .** Bring water. Wear hiking boots\, preferably waterproof with good soles
  and traction devices and bring poles (optional).\n- Dogs are not allowed 
 on hikes unless specified.\nThese hikes are publicized first to SMC member
 s and then advertised to the public one week before a hike. There is a lim
 it of 25 participants\, so pre-registration is required at least two days 
 before a hike to sign the liability waiver online and allow lists to be se
 nt to hike leaders. If you have registered and then find you cannot attend
 \, please cancel your order online.\n**Repeated no shows without prior can
 cellation will result in removal from list.**\n\n**To become a current mem
 ber visit [[https://www.somocon.org/membership/](https://www.somocon.org/m
 embership/)](https://www.somocon.org/membership/).**
