SUMMARY:Building Montclair in LEGO
DESCRIPTION:Join architect Michael Schwartz of Building Blocks Workshops for a hands-on family session using over 100\,000 LEGO™ bricks. Families learn basic architectural principles as they recreate Montclair landmarks such as the Museum\, the library\, and historic homes. Pick a favorite local structure to build together as a scale model. At the end of the session\, each family places their building on a large-scale map to create a shared view of our community. \nCo-presented with Montclair History Center in conjunction with Building Blocks Workshops. \nBuilding Montclair in LEGO™ has two sessions to choose from. If our 1–3 p.m. session is full\, check our 4–6 p.m. session here. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/building-montclair-in-lego-2/
LOCATION:Montclair Art Museum\, 3 South Mountain Ave\, Montclair\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Kids & Families
