X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Local News": "https://montclairlocal.news/event/in-bloom-an-international-womens-day-workshop-at-the-mc-hotel/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairlocal
X-SOURCE:Montclair Local News
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T170000
DTSTAMP:20260304T214105
CREATED:20260303T063948Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T063948Z
UID:10138196-1772982000-1772989200@montclairlocal.news
SUMMARY:In Bloom: An International Women's Day Workshop at the MC Hotel
DESCRIPTION:Get into your body\nWe will begin with a mini yoga stretch session to help you arrive\, soften\, and wake up your presence. Expect gentle stretches\, simple movement\, and space to settle into yourself before the rest of the experience unfolds. \nGet into your inner world\nYou will be guided through a metta meditation\, giving you time to pause\, reflect\, and reconnect with yourself in a supportive and grounded way. \nGet into your community\nWe will take part in an interactive workshop and shared conversation designed to deepen self-love\, build connection\, and remind you that you are not alone in what you are moving through. \nGet into the beauty of nature\nYou will receive a bouquet from Sophie’s Garden to take home\, a tangible reminder of growth\, intention\, and care. \nAll of this takes place in the stunning Gatsby Room at the MC Hotel\, with sweeping views of New York City. A setting that invites you to slow down\, expand\, and feel inspired. 🌸 \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/in-bloom-an-international-womens-day-workshop-at-the-mc-hotel/
LOCATION:THE MC HOTEL\, 690 BLOOMFIELD AVE\, MONTCLAIR\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairlocal.news/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/page-3-scaled.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Local News": "https://montclairlocal.news/event/beat-the-sunday-scaries-with-beam/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairlocal
X-SOURCE:Montclair Local News
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T180000
DTSTAMP:20260304T214105
CREATED:20260220T222800Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T222800Z
UID:10138168-1772982000-1772992800@montclairlocal.news
SUMMARY:Beat the Sunday Scaries with BEAM
DESCRIPTION:Is work getting you down? Do you dread going back to your job on Mondays\, or any day? \nWhether you’re stuck in the grind\, just entering the workforce\, recently laid off\, or struggling to land your dream role\, you’re not alone! \nPlease join us on Sunday\, March 8th\, 3–6pm in Montclair\, to beat the “Sunday Scaries” – that sinking feeling in our stomach as Monday approaches. We invite you to drop by for a friendly group to say hi and connect. \nThis is not a hiring event – and is not affiliated with any employer or agency. We’re just local community members looking to boost and strengthen one another. \nThis is not a “Hello\, My Name Is” networking event. We’re serious about helping one another build real connections\, figuring out how we can support one another\, getting through the work week together\, and navigating the “work cost” of living. \nWe’ll tell stories and ask each other questions about work and life. We’ll play an icebreaker game for fun. We’ll have a laid-off HR recruiter\, in case anyone wants insider tips. \nGet off Linkedln and come meet others IRL – in real life!\n– Bond with other Essex County folks who face similar work issues.\n– Chat about beating the corporate grind\, transitioning careers\, working parenthood\, unemployment\, job survival – or whatever work+life topics are on your mind.\n– Ask about tips for resumes\, job searching\, interviewing\, seeking a raise\, and salary negotiations. \nEven though this meeting is located at a church\, we’re completely nonreligious and aren’t looking to push an agenda – just mutual support\, maybe ongoing in future meetings if participants want. All are welcome – working or not\, any industry\, any age\, etc. \nLocation: 153 Park Street in Montclair\, entrance on the right-hand side of the First Lutheran Church building\, near Montclair High School. Parking is free. Refreshments will be served! Please RSVP online at tinyurl.com/beam-scaries ! \nBEAM (Building Essex Area Mutuality\, beamnj.org) is a group of community members in the Essex County\, NJ area who organize mutual support\, aid\, education\, and community action to meet needs\, grow connections\, and challenge systems of exploitation and harm. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/beat-the-sunday-scaries-with-beam/
LOCATION:153 Park St\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, 153 Park St.\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Community
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://montclairlocal.news/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/BEAM-logo.png
ORGANIZER;CN="BEAM %E2%80%93 Building Essex Area Mutuality":MAILTO:hi@beamnj.org
END:VEVENT
