X-SOURCE-URLS:{"First Congregational Church Montclair": "https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:fcc_montclair
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T203000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;COUNT=3;BYDAY=WE
DTSTAMP:20260305T024126Z
UID:2j39bl8h8612qmbdairh547q80@google.com
CREATED:20260224T181527Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>How do we live compassionately in a time of violence a
 nd despair? What can we do with our private disappointments and the anger t
 hat we feel in such an unjust world? These are the questions many of us car
 ry on our hearts.  This Lent\, we will gather to explore them with Francisc
 an friar\,Richard Rohr\, as he turns to the writings of the Hebrew prophets
  to offer us a path forward today.<br><br>The prophets' writings reflect th
 e full spectrum of human maturity.  In almost every case their criticism of
  culture and institutions take them on a journey from anger to sadness and 
 ultimately\, to compassion. They confront evil and injustice in a way that 
 acknowledges the wholeness of history\, the interconnectedness of every liv
 ing being\, and the reality of divine and universal love.  In doing so\, th
 ey set the stage for Jesus\, who follows this identical pattern. <br><br>Th
 is Lent\, join Rev. Ann for three Zoom sessions to explore what this ancien
 t wisdom has to teach us in our own time of outrage and heartbreak.<b><u><s
 pan> We encourage you to read the book to prepare for this study.  You can 
 order it online <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/tra
 ck/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=da482d4d86&e=d2d6ac503b" target="_b
 lank"><span>HERE</span></a> or through your favorite bookstore.</span></u><
 /b> </span></p><p><b><span>To join the class click the</span></b><span> <a 
 href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca7
 44bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=b628613b45&e=d2d6ac503b" target="_blank"><span>ZOOM LI
 NK HERE</span></a><br><br></span><b><span>We look forward to taking this Le
 nten journey together.</span></b></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T181805Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Lenten Study "The Tears of Things - Wednesday evenings March 11\,18
 \,25 @7:30pm on Zoom
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
