X-SOURCE:Montclair Public Library
DTSTART:20260313T200000Z
DTEND:20260313T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260313T000000Z
SUMMARY:Be Internet Awesome: Internet Safety For Kids (2nd-5th Graders)
DESCRIPTION:In today's digital landscape\, children need more than just 
 access -- they need guidance\, values\, and tools to navigate it 
 responsibly. That's where Be Internet Awesome comes in! In this program 
 series\, they'll learn the five Pillars: Smart\, Alert\, Strong\, Kind\, 
 and Brave. These Pillars teach kids to think critically\, protect their 
 privacy\, stand up to cyberbullying\, and build a culture of respect and 
 empathy online. \n\nParents are encouraged to join our sessions. We will 
 have some take-home materials available after each session to continue the 
 learning at home! \n\nThis session will cover the pillar: KIND\n\nWhat the 
 kids will learn: Kids explore how empathy helps them get along with others 
 online and how they can be upstanders when they see mean behavior.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Storytime Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs, Computers & Technology
UID:LibCal-10306-16172191
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16172191
END:VEVENT
