SUMMARY:NJ Code & Coffee meetup - March
DESCRIPTION:NJ Code & Coffee\nCalling all New Jersey techies to the **NJ C
 ode and Coffee** tech community meetup at the EqualSpace ES550 Tech & Inno
 vation campus!\n\nCode and Coffee is an inclusive\, informal networking/co
 -working session for those in tech (and the tech-curious).\nThat includes 
 operators\, founders\, and investors. Developers\, data engineers\, UX/UI 
 designers\, data scientists\, product managers\, software engineers\, solu
 tion architects... **all are welcome!**\n\nPeople of all skill and experie
 nce levels can attend\, we love it that way. Many people (optionally) brin
 g projects to work on\, and many other people (optionally) socialize the e
 ntire time. It's entirely up to you!\n\nCome grab a cup of coffee and meet
  new people\, share stories\, find collaborators\, talk about everything t
 ech\, talk about everything NOT tech\, take a break from job applications\
 , get away from the computer screen\, make connections\, make conversation
 \, **make friends!**\n\n**Agenda:**\n**2pm:** Doors open\, networking star
 ts\n**2:30pm:** Intro circle\n**3pm:** networking continues\n**5pm:** even
 t ends\n\n**The Intro Circle**\n**Near the beginning of the event (about 2
 :30 pm)\, we will do a standup in a circle:**\nWe first talk about organiz
 er announcements\, updates\, and logistics. Then we go around the circle w
 here each person says:\n\n* your name and job title/ role in tech/ tech st
 ack\,\n* What you can help others with\,\n* What you would like help with\
 ,\n* Job opportunities you're hiring for OR announce that you are looking 
 for one. If none\, that's cool.\n\nAfter the introduction circle\, everyth
 ing is self-organized.\n\n**Community Discord - come hang out before and a
 fter!:**\n[www.codeandcoffee.chat](www.codeandcoffee.chat)\n\n**The Venue*
 *\nEqual Space is a premium share-space created with multicultural busines
 s owners in mind\, =SPACE equips founders with resources\, programming and
  a powerful network.\n\nHeadquartered in the City of Newark\, their share-
 space provides resources for startups\, coaching for tech companies\, and 
 a wealth of intellectuals to collaborate and build with. The next wave in 
 enterprises is being born within their walls. Become a part of the story: 
 [EqualSpace.co/](https://equalspace.co/)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/nj-code-coffee/events/313115551/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260129T190227Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260129T190227Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
