X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Arts
DESCRIPTION:Don’t miss this rare opportunity to learn from one of the most
  influential voices in modern jazz drumming.\nLegendary jazz drummer Bill
 y Hart\, known for his work with Herbie Hancock\, Stan Getz\, and countle
 ss others\, leads a dynamic masterclass at the Cali School of Music.\nBil
 ly Hart is one of the most influential jazz drummers of his generation\, 
 celebrated for his versatility across straight-ahead\, avant-garde\, and 
 popular styles. He has released 12 albums as a leader and appeared on mor
 e than 600 recordings\, working with legends such as Herbie Hancock\, Mil
 es Davis\, Wes Montgomery\, Stan Getz\, and Charles Lloyd. A founding mem
 ber of Quest and a longtime member of the Cookers\, Hart also leads his o
 wn acclaimed quartet. Born in Washington\, D.C.\, he began performing as 
 a teenager with Buck Hill and Shirley Horn before touring in the 1960s wi
 th Jimmy Smith\, Wes Montgomery\, and Eddie Harris. Since then\, his care
 er has spanned collaborations with both jazz icons and experimental innov
 ators.\n\nHosted by: The College of the Arts\n\nAdditional Information ca
 n be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12291768
DTEND:20260316T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260305T024118Z
DTSTART:20260316T180000Z
GEO:40.858220;-74.199660
LOCATION:Leshowitz Recital Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CALI SCHOOL OF MUSIC | Billy Hart | Jazz Drum Faculty Masterclass
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12291768
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12291768
X-HOSTS:The College of the Arts
END:VEVENT
