DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T110000
SUMMARY:Let's Walk!! in Belleville Park
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nLet’s get out and enjoy nature by walking abou
 t 3 miles in Belleville Park.\n\nWe will also check out the nearby Essex H
 udson Greenway and Branch Brook Park. Wear comfortable shoes and bring som
 e water!\n\nBelleville Park is a mid-sized\, 32.70-acre park designed by t
 he Olmsteds with a playground\, bocce courts\, ball fields & a jogging pat
 h. It is bordered by Belleville and Parkside Avenues and Mill Street along
  the Second River\, which was once a part of the Morris Canal.\n\n**We sta
 rt promptly\, so please arrive at least 5 minutes before the start.**\nRai
 n or extreme weather will cancel the event.\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us 
 for a hike/walk\, please understand that you are responsible for your own 
 preparedness and well-being and will hold no one else liable in case of in
 jury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313099522/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260128T193105Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260128T193105Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: South Mountain Conservancy": "https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313529430/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_somocon
X-SOURCE:Meetup: South Mountain Conservancy
UID:event_313529430@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260305T024114Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T130000
SUMMARY:Orange & Tulip Springs w/ Donna ~5 miles
DESCRIPTION:South Mountain Conservancy Activities Meetup Group\nMeet 9:30 
 at Tulip Springs. 6 Mile hike lower Orange to upper Orange and then some.\
 n\nBring snacks\, water\, poles\, spikes if needed. Moderate pace.\n\n**Le
 ader**: Donna Burkat- 973-454-5635 call or text if you need to cancel.\n\n
 \\*\\*\\* In registering for this or any other South Mountain Conservancy 
 (SMC) programs in 2026 online\, I hereby release and agree to hold the SMC
 \, its volunteers\, staff and Board of Trustees\, harmless from and waive 
 on behalf of myself\, my heirs\, and any personal representatives any and 
 all causes of action\, claims\, demands\, damages\, costs\, expenses and c
 ompensation for damage or loss to myself and/or property that may be cause
 d by any act\, or failure to act\, in this SMC activity\, or that may othe
 rwise arise in any way in connection with any other SMC activity. I unders
 tand that this release discharges the SMC from any liability or claim that
  I\, my heirs\, or any personal representatives\, may have against the SMC
  with respect to any bodily injury\, illness\, death\, medical treatment\,
  or property damage that may arise from\, or in connection to\, any SMC pr
 ogram. This liability waiver and release extends to the SMC along with Ess
 ex County and its staff and any other affiliated organization or SMC partn
 er. I also understand that by signing below I approve the possible use of 
 photos of me at this SMC event on social media or in promotional materials
 .\n**BY REGISTERING FOR THIS HIKE I attest I am in good health and attest 
 that I: Am not experiencing any symptoms of illness such as cough\, shortn
 ess of breath or difficulty breathing\, fever\, chills\, repeated shaking 
 with chills\, muscle pain\, headache\, sore throat\, or new loss of taste 
 or smell.**\n**Am following all CDC recommended guidelines\, above\, and l
 imiting my exposure to the novel coronavirus/COVID-19.**\n\\# Arrival\\\, 
 Weather\\\, & Cancellations\nPlease come to the starting point 10 minutes 
 ahead of time so the hike can start promptly. Times are our best estimates
 \; they can vary depending on conditions\, and the size and pace of a grou
 p. If you have any questions\, call the leader. **Temperatures above 90 de
 grees and steady rain cancels\, but intermittent drizzle does not. You wil
 l *not* be notified.** **Bring water. Wear hiking boots\, preferably water
 proof with good soles and traction devices and bring poles (optional).** D
 ogs are not allowed on hikes unless specified.\nThese hikes are publicized
  first to SMC members and then advertised to the public one week before a 
 hike. There is a limit of 25 participants\, so pre-registration is require
 d at least two days before a hike to sign the liability waiver online and 
 allow lists to be sent to hike leaders. If you have registered and then fi
 nd you cannot attend\, please cancel your order online. **Repeated no show
 s without prior cancellation will result in removal from list.**\n**To bec
 ome a current member visit [[https://www.somocon.org/membership/](https://
 www.somocon.org/membership/)]([https://www.somocon.org/membership/](https:
 //www.somocon.org/membership/)).**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313529430/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260225T212850Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T212850Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
