DESCRIPTION:Looking  for  a  nice  day  out  with  your  friends?  Join  u
 s  on  an easy  hike  at Turkey Mountain in  Montville Township. This  5.
 4  mile  hike  offers multiple viewpoints\, a waterfall\, and an area to 
 explore ruins of an old stone home!\nHow do I sign-up?\n\nRegister on Fus
 ion\, or in the Student Recreation Center main office or over the phone (
 973-655-3340).\nCost for Students  $10 \; Faculty/Staff $20\n\nWhere and 
 when?\n\nSunday\, March 29 2026\n10 a.m. - 5 p.m.\nBegins at Student Recr
 eation Center\n\nWhat to bring: Water\, Lunch\, and Boots or Sneakers\nPo
 tential Hazards: Unpredictable weather changes\, sunburn/heat exhaustion\
 , limited vision\, dehydration\, allergic reactions/poisonous plants\, in
 sect bites\, and injury by running\, including sprains\, lacerations\, ab
 rasions and fractures.\n\nHosted by: Campus Recreation\n\nAdditional Info
 rmation can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12
 209673
