UID:TU2005886228
DTSTAMP:20260303T200314Z
SUMMARY:Midday MeetUp - Jews and Baseball\, A Love Affair
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Jews and Baseball\, A Love Affair**  \n  \nA 
 monthly gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Cater
 ed Lunch (free)  \n12:30pm Featured Program   \n  \nJoin baseball historia
 n Sam Bernstein for a lively survey of Jewish involvement in America’s N
 ational Pastime.  \n  \nCost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per pers
 on to offset costs. (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n 
  \n**RSVP:** Required so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei.
 easyshul.com/events/6967e303368f110026c0c410  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\; 
 PreSchool Families should use their fob to access the building.  \n  \n**A
 bout the Program**  \nUsing audio and video\, *Jews and Baseball* explores
  the origins of the game and the impact Jewish players\, owners\, and inno
 vators have had on its evolution. The program highlights figures such as H
 ank Greenberg\, Sandy Koufax\, Barney Dreyfuss\, Bud Selig\, Lou Boudreau\
 , Marvin Miller\, as well as the game's current Jewish stars. It also delv
 es into topics including antisemitism in the sport\, baseball’s growth i
 n Israel\, and the lore of the “Koufax Curse.”  \n  \n**About Sam Bern
 stein**  \nSam Bernstein is a retired Social Worker who has published many
  articles on baseball history. He received a BA in History from the Americ
 an University and an MSW from Adelphi University. After a career serving t
 he Jewish community at JCCs and Jewish Family Service\, Sam worked for the
  Elizabeth Public Schools and as an Instructor in Social Work for Rutgers 
 University. He was raised in Malverne\, NY and moved to New Jersey with hi
 s wife Maureen in 1999.  \n  \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: ht
 tps://shomrei.org/calendar/midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questions?** Co
 ntact June Zimmerman\,   \nVP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  \
 n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LOCATION:Social Hall
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
