X-SOURCE-ID:shomrei_emunah
X-SOURCE:Congregation Shomrei Emunah
URL:https://shomrei.org/calendar/
UID:TU2007101531
DTSTAMP:20260303T200314Z
SUMMARY:Midday MeetUp - Bonnie Rapp\, Best of Broadway
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Bonnie Rapp\, Best of Broadway   \nA monthly 
 gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Catered Lunch
  (free)  \n12:30pm Featured Program   \n  \nExperience *The Best of Broadw
 ay* as Bonnie Rapp brings to life unforgettable moments from Tony Award–
 winning musicals. Relive the golden age of musical theatre through beloved
  classics and timeless melodies by legendary composers such as Rodgers and
  Hammerstein\, Lerner and Loewe\, Frank Loesser\, Irving Berlin and more! 
  \n  \nCost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per person to offset cost
 s. (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n  \n**RSVP:** Requ
 ired so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei.easyshul.com/even
 ts/6967e6f2368f110026c0c486  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\; PreSchool Familie
 s should use their fob to access the building.  \n About Bonnie Rapp**  \n
 Bonnie had the honor of performing the lead role of Christine Daaé in the
  National Tour/San Francisco Company of Andrew Lloyd Webber's The Phantom 
 of the Opera. Some of Bonnie’s favorite roles include Maria in The Sound
  of Music\, Kate in Kiss Me\, Kate\, Cinderella in Rodgers and Hammerstein
 ’s Cinderella\, Louise in Gypsy and Sister Amnesia and Sister Leo in Nun
 sense\, Nunsense II and Nunsense Jamboree. In addition\, Bonnie has appear
 ed in numerous galas\, fundraisers\, and Broadway concerts\, including per
 formances at Lincoln Center's Avery Fisher Hall.  \n  \nFor the past decad
 e\, Bonnie has devoted her talents to providing live musical entertainment
  for a wide range of audiences\, including corporate and community events\
 , libraries\, private celebrations\, JCCs\, and residents of independent l
 iving\, assisted living\, nursing homes\, and memory care communities.  \n
   \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: https://shomrei.org/calendar/
 midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questions?** Contact June Zimmerman\,   \n
 VP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LOCATION:Social Hall
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
